1
00:00:28,020 --> 00:00:32,800
[Extremely Perilous Love]

2
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,400
[Episode 6]

3
00:00:34,480 --> 00:00:36,440
[Madam Is in Trouble]

4
00:00:40,160 --> 00:00:41,480
What are you looking for?

5
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,480
I just want to know more about

6
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:53,800
your preferences.

7
00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:55,720
So that it's easier for you to kill me.

8
00:00:58,360 --> 00:00:59,640
General, you must be kidding.

9
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:02,960
It's true that I am new to being a wife,

10
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,280
and I have many shortcomings,

11
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:07,440
but how could I
have the intention to harm you?

12
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:09,160
The poison in the wine,

13
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:11,640
the intended
approach on our wedding night,

14
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,040
as well as

15
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:15,200
the carriage beam that you sabotaged.

16
00:01:15,960 --> 00:01:19,600
How do you explain all that?

17
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,480
I drank the wine as well.

18
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:27,320
Why was I unharmed?

19
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:29,960
For a couple to
be intimate on the wedding night,

20
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,600
it's perfectly reasonable.

21
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:34,040
The talk of
the carriage is even more ridiculous.

22
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,200
If I had any
malicious intent toward you,

23
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,320
why is it that I am
the one who got hurt in the end?

24
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:40,160
General.

25
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:42,400
Why do you want to accuse me

26
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:43,880
of so many baseless charges?

27
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,560
I have no evidence,

28
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:48,800
so I'll stop arguing with you.

29
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,760
I'm just curious.

30
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,720
What is your next plan?

31
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,120
You must be joking, General.

32
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:57,800
How can there be any next plan?

33
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,080
Prime Minister Xu wants you to kill me.

34
00:01:59,080 --> 00:01:59,960
How is that possible?

35
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:01,560
Then, there must be another plan.

36
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,480
Could it be that

37
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:09,200
you want the pass token
to the viewing platform?

38
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,640
What token?

39
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,320
I just feel that

40
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,440
you're always busy
with government affairs,

41
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,400
so I want to find more books

42
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:33,000
that you love to read

43
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,280
to learn more about you.

44
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:38,500
[The Rules of Students]

45
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,200
Since you want to understand me,

46
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:51,880
there's no need for covert inquiries.

47
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,800
Just ask directly,

48
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,880
and I will tell you myself.

49
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,640
My injury is not healed yet.

50
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:09,560
Please give me some more time, General.

51
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,100
These are the people

52
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:21,040
who participated
in the assassination last time.

53
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,640
What a good son-in-law.

54
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:28,200
I am well aware of
the reciprocating culture.

55
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,420
I won't spare anyone

56
00:03:31,940 --> 00:03:33,760
who dares to harm Yin.

57
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,800
General, you protect Madam so well,

58
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,840
yet she doesn't know anything about it.

59
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:39,960
You're being too nosy.

60
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:40,840
Yes.

61
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:41,760
General.

62
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,040
We should go to the barracks now.

63
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:44,280
Where's Qingqing?

64
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:45,760
She sneaked out.

65
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:47,160
I've sent someone
to protect her secretly.

66
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:55,040
[Anfu Hall]

67
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,280
[Seal]

68
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:02,800
Father.

69
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,520
Once I obtain
the token to the viewing platform,

70
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,960
I can make them fight each other,

71
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,000
and I can take revenge for you.

72
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,040
Young master.

73
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:26,280
What's wrong with you?

74
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,840
I'm having a chest pain.

75
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,400
Give me your hand.

76
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:51,960
Young lady, your
medical skills are exceptional.

77
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,200
Thank you for saving me.

78
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,160
Don't mention it.

79
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,120
May I know your name?

80
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,840
Who is this young lady?

81
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:48,560
Grandmother.

82
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,400
It's her.

83
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,560
She is full of evil spirits.

84
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:52,680
Old Madam.

85
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,160
Not only is this
evil spirit harmful to your body,

86
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:58,160
but it may also pose a threat to
the whole General's Manor in the future.

87
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,760
What is Mu Yuexi up to again?

88
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:04,080
Quick, remove the evil spirits from her.

89
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,540
May heaven protect the General's Manor

90
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:15,920
from illness and disaster.

91
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,480
No illness, no disaster.

92
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,080
Why is she here?

93
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:44,120
Greetings, grandmother.

94
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:46,360
Shengming, you've returned.

95
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:48,480
Grandmother.

96
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,000
There's such a huge set up.

97
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:52,400
What's going on here?

98
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,480
Shengming, you don't know,

99
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,920
this newlywed bride of Shenghan,

100
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,160
is filled with evil spirits.

101
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:01,200
The Taoist master
is currently removing them for her.

102
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,760
She's actually Shenghan's newlywed wife.

103
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,200
Grandmother.

104
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,720
Today's sun is scorching.

105
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:11,840
If she's under the sun for too long,

106
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:13,320
it could be fatal.

107
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,120
You don't need to say more.

108
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,040
The Taoist master knows what he's doing.

109
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,240
Grandmother.

110
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,960
There are heavy evil spirits here.

111
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:21,880
Since you're not well,

112
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:24,600
it's better if I help
you back to your room to rest.

113
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:49,040
Stop the carriage.

114
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:51,520
General.

115
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:52,600
There's news from the manor.

116
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,400
Madam is in trouble.

117
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,240
It's all your doing.

118
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:59,160
If only you had left
the General's Manor earlier,

119
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,240
you wouldn't have to suffer so much.

120
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,840
General went to the barracks today,

121
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:07,120
so there's no one to save you.

122
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:09,480
Let me bring you to your end.

123
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,720
You're finally awake.

124
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:31,120
Thank you for saving me.

125
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:32,960
Didn't you save me too?

126
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,120
We're on equal terms now.

127
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,400
Young master,
what is your true identity?

128
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,360
I'm Gu Shengming.

129
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,320
I've just returned from working abroad.

130
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,400
I missed
the wedding of you and Shenghan.

131
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,480
You're Gu Shenghan's younger brother.

132
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:51,000
Greetings, Shengming.

133
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,000
This jade pendant...

134
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,040
What's wrong with you?

135
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:10,120
Why are you so seriously injured?

136
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:35,880
This jade pendant

137
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:37,880
is something
I've worn since I was young.

138
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,480
This jade pendant is truly special.

139
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,160
Could it be that

140
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:54,480
she mistook me for Gu Shenghan?

141
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:11,160
What history
did they share in that place?

142
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,440
Since the two of you haven't
revealed your identity to each other,

143
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:16,920
I still stand a chance.

144
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:21,840
This jade pendant
was a gift from my grandmother.

145
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:23,720
It has never left my side.

146
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:28,360
Have you ever been to
a thatched hut on Qingyang Mountain?

147
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:31,360
Is that hut important to you?

148
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:34,960
It's just things
that happened in the past.

149
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,400
Regarding what
happened in the hut last time,

150
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,200
I can't speak of it.

151
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,000
But that place

152
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:49,320
has always been on my mind.

153
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:57,600
How did Gu Shengming know
the things that happened in the hut?

154
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:01,640
And you,

155
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,000
Yin.

156
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,520
You actually
mistook me for someone else.

157
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:14,920
♪Fine rain infiltrates
the deep night, awakening the jasmine♪

158
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:18,840
♪Two swallows build nests on the beam♪

159
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:21,200
♪Carrying fresh mud in their beaks♪

160
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:27,600
♪Gazing into the distance,
the path is filled with thriving grass♪

161
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:33,800
♪The beautiful scene
feels undeserved by you♪

162
00:12:35,180 --> 00:12:37,500
♪The night wind suddenly rises♪

163
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,500
♪Ruffling the rippling pool water♪

164
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:45,340
♪The full moon is what I fear the most♪

165
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:47,820
♪Similar smiles♪

166
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:52,180
♪Conceal varying degrees of familiarity♪

167
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:57,820
♪Emotions overflow
deeply; how much do you know♪

168
00:12:57,820 --> 00:13:00,180
♪I offer you a branch of jasmine♪

169
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:03,980
♪May you never leave;
we rely on each other from dawn to dusk♪

170
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:06,180
♪How easily we part, unbeknownst to us♪

171
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:09,820
♪When we meet, there is
no predetermined time to return♪

